FDBwordsets
  • Reference

Treiman et al (1990), Nonword set.

This data set gathered from the source appendix includes 48 nonwords with either high or low frequency.

tgb1990

Format

A data.frame with 48 rows and 3 variables:

nonwords

Orthographic representation of nonwords.

phon_rep

Phonological representation with adjusted phonological symbols.

frequency

Word frequency bin: H (high) or L (low).

Source

Treiman, R., Goswami, U., & Bruck, M. (1990). Not all nonwords are alike: Implications for reading development and theory. Memory & Cognition, 18(6), 559-567. doi:10.3758/BF03197098

Details

See source paper for details.
